5|$|During the 1992 UEFA European Football Championship (commonly called Euro 1992), Malmö Stadion hosted three {{matches in}} Group 1, which {{comprised}} the national teams of Sweden, Denmark, England and France. None of the matches played in Malmö involved Sweden, however, as the <b>host</b> <b>nation</b> played {{all of their}} matches at Råsunda, a stadium {{in the capital city}} Stockholm.|$|E
